I think a work environment

331
00:46:04,475 --> 00:46:07,449
where I interact less with others
would be better.

332
00:46:07,778 --> 00:46:10,018
For everyone's benefit.

333
00:46:11,214 --> 00:46:13,989
That's a very responsible attitude.

334
00:46:23,231 --> 00:46:26,164
Oh, Nia... meet Dominic,
our new illustrator.

335
00:46:26,264 --> 00:46:30,468
Dominic, this is Nia, she works in text.
You'll be interpreting her words.

336
00:46:30,568 --> 00:46:34,771
- It's very nice to meet you, Nia.
- Welcome to Atmos.

337
00:46:34,871 --> 00:46:37,079
Follow me.

338
00:47:38,268 --> 00:47:43,640
I also design rockets. I could have been
an engineer, but I lacked patience.

339
00:47:43,740 --> 00:47:47,711
I think working at Atmos
is a vitally important job.

340
00:47:47,811 --> 00:47:51,720
Science is a process
and often leads to dead-ends.

341
00:47:52,049 --> 00:47:53,784
But here...

342
00:47:53,884 --> 00:47:57,922
we're delivering the answers,
we're educating people.

343
00:47:58,022 --> 00:48:01,759
Knowledge is sacred,
and Atmos is the new scripture.

344
00:48:01,859 --> 00:48:04,828
If you think about it,
we're kind of like preachers.

345
00:48:04,928 --> 00:48:06,531
Where did you study?

346
00:48:06,631 --> 00:48:09,801
I'm self-taught. I've always drawn
pictures ever since I was a child.

347
00:48:09,901 --> 00:48:14,509
One of my guardians, Barnabas,
nicknamed me Little Da Vinci.

348
00:48:15,439 --> 00:48:18,308
Did you hear? Zoe was inseminated.

349
00:48:18,408 --> 00:48:20,979
It means she's clean.
She didn't catch the bug from Silas.

350
00:48:21,079 --> 00:48:24,762
- That means we're probably clean, too.
- I'm definitely clean.

351
00:48:24,862 --> 00:48:27,422
I donated blood last week.

352
00:49:12,662 --> 00:49:14,536
Silas?

353
00:49:17,334 --> 00:49:19,174
Jonas?

354
00:49:25,942 --> 00:49:28,078
You okay?

355
00:49:28,178 --> 00:49:29,747
Okay.

356
00:49:30,597 --> 00:49:32,571
Do you want to take a walk?

357
00:49:39,656 --> 00:49:41,929
I miss her.

358
00:49:43,092 --> 00:49:47,570
I don't know, it felt so good
to be around her that...

359
00:49:48,598 --> 00:49:52,307
we were nearly tripping up
and I couldn't see...

360
00:49:53,003 --> 00:49:55,605
couldn't see anything bad
happening to her.

361
00:49:55,705 --> 00:49:58,141
You two were in love with each other.

362
00:49:58,241 --> 00:50:01,479
That's very clear.
You were right to end it though.

363
00:50:01,579 --> 00:50:04,115
I think dealing with this disease
on your own is hard enough,

364
00:50:04,215 --> 00:50:07,246
coupling would just make it unbearable.

365
00:50:13,390 --> 00:50:15,459
You know...

366
00:50:15,559 --> 00:50:17,766
about a year ago...

367
00:50:18,562 --> 00:50:21,803
I also made a connection with a woman.

368
00:50:24,167 --> 00:50:27,376
Though, it didn't end well.

369
00:50:33,076 --> 00:50:35,350
So sorry.

370
00:50:38,782 --> 00:50:42,457
Your friend, what stage is she?

371
00:50:43,086 --> 00:50:46,591
She's self-diagnosed.
She's fighting the bug without drugs.

372
00:50:46,691 --> 00:50:49,163
She's a "hider."

373
00:50:52,262 --> 00:50:56,833
Not many people can do that successfully.
I think hiders are...

374
00:50:56,933 --> 00:50:58,836
I think they are wired differently.

375
00:50:58,936 --> 00:51:02,239
You know we have one in our group.
Bess. She's a...

376
00:51:02,339 --> 00:51:05,542
she's a doctor at the den, of all places.

377
00:51:05,642 --> 00:51:08,813
Listen, I'm part of a group.
A support group.

378
00:51:08,913 --> 00:51:11,315
With Bess and others from my work.

379
00:51:11,415 --> 00:51:14,718
To talk openly about how we feel.

380
00:51:14,818 --> 00:51:17,587
If you're interested I'll vouch for you.

381
00:51:17,687 --> 00:51:19,961
It might help.

382
00:51:21,424 --> 00:51:23,966
I'd be willing to try.

383
00:51:25,895 --> 00:51:27,736
Great.

384
00:51:32,068 --> 00:51:35,839
Nia, it's me again. Until you give me
some text to work with, I am idle,

385
00:51:35,939 --> 00:51:39,147
and that doesn't seem
like a very good use of my time.

386
00:51:40,944 --> 00:51:42,246
I'm almost finished, Dominic.

387
00:51:42,346 --> 00:51:44,715
All the other illustrators
received their pieces hours ago...

388
00:51:44,815 --> 00:51:46,972
I'm almost finished, Dominic.

389
00:51:51,788 --> 00:51:54,196
But I appreciate your patience.

390
00:51:55,292 --> 00:51:57,499
Of course.

391
00:52:52,816 --> 00:52:55,485
Silas, you made it.

392
00:52:55,585 --> 00:52:57,321
This is great. I'm glad you're here.

393
00:52:57,421 --> 00:53:00,624
Everybody, this is Silas.
The one I was telling you about.

394
00:53:00,724 --> 00:53:03,594
Silas, this is Bess. Peter and Thomas.

395
00:53:03,694 --> 00:53:05,929
Gilead, Max and Alice.

396
00:53:06,029 --> 00:53:08,338
Come take a seat.

397
00:53:10,538 --> 00:53:12,836
