brought in commit suicide.

410
00:54:00,618 --> 00:54:04,355
The staff encourages it
and stand by while it happens.

411
00:54:04,455 --> 00:54:06,157
And that's the preferable option anyway.

412
00:54:06,257 --> 00:54:09,093
Compared to electro restraints
and all the other methods of treatment.

413
00:54:09,193 --> 00:54:12,367
But there is value in living.

414
00:54:14,981 --> 00:54:17,918
Being a hider reminds you of that.

415
00:54:18,018 --> 00:54:20,937
I still don't know how you do it.

416
00:54:21,037 --> 00:54:24,212
Working for health and safety
is hard enough.

417
00:54:25,875 --> 00:54:29,947
Yes, it's difficult to see things
and not be moved.

418
00:54:30,047 --> 00:54:33,883
But that's what being
a hider is all about.

419
00:54:33,983 --> 00:54:36,603
So you do small things to help.

420
00:54:36,703 --> 00:54:39,406
Just looking someone in the eyes,

421
00:54:39,506 --> 00:54:44,115
can make them feel they're not alone.
Give them hope.

422
00:54:45,462 --> 00:54:49,599
But under no circumstances
do you interfere.

423
00:54:49,699 --> 00:54:55,010
You have to tell yourself, do not risk
your job, do not risk your life.

424
00:54:58,341 --> 00:55:02,150
But why stay in a position
where you feel so much risk?

425
00:55:02,612 --> 00:55:07,422
- You could ask to be reassigned.
- I'd rather be with people who feel.

426
00:55:08,218 --> 00:55:10,754
Who feel intensely.

427
00:55:11,254 --> 00:55:15,593
It reminds me of who I am
and why I choose to keep on living.

428
00:55:15,693 --> 00:55:19,196
Everybody says it's not contagious.

429
00:55:19,596 --> 00:55:23,566
But after all these years
as awful as it is,

430
00:55:23,666 --> 00:55:26,936
everyday I feel a stronger...

431
00:55:27,036 --> 00:55:30,245
affinity with other people.

432
00:55:32,275 --> 00:55:34,844
See I don't believe all the research.

433
00:55:34,944 --> 00:55:37,347
Feelings engender feelings.

434
00:55:37,447 --> 00:55:40,751
S.O.S. isn't even a disease,
that's what they say but...

435
00:55:40,851 --> 00:55:44,755
switched off is something they do
to us between conception and birth.

436
00:55:44,855 --> 00:55:46,891
S.O.S. is who we really are and...

437
00:55:46,991 --> 00:55:50,394
the inhibitors are just
another attempt to squash that.

438
00:55:50,494 --> 00:55:53,763
- I don't know.
- It's so hard.

439
00:55:53,863 --> 00:55:56,199
It's lonely.

440
00:55:56,499 --> 00:56:00,370
At least with the inhibitors
I can get by but now...

441
00:56:00,470 --> 00:56:03,206
I would rather feel nothing.

442
00:56:03,506 --> 00:56:06,615
Nothing is better than this.

443
00:57:46,042 --> 00:57:48,667
It's okay. It's okay.

444
00:59:15,565 --> 00:59:19,870
I could never have imagined
what love felt like. It's strange...

445
00:59:20,470 --> 00:59:23,006
like a little tornado going around and...

446
00:59:23,106 --> 00:59:24,831
Yeah.

447
00:59:27,810 --> 00:59:30,736
That's why I was so scared of it at first.

448
00:59:35,852 --> 00:59:39,022
It's about giving,
I want you to take everything,

449
00:59:39,122 --> 00:59:42,860
I don't even know what it is,
I just want you to take it from me.

450
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:44,794
I just want to...

451
00:59:44,894 --> 00:59:47,102
I want to run.

452
00:59:49,766 --> 00:59:52,201
I want to run... both of us...

453
00:59:52,301 --> 00:59:55,734
as fast as we can, outside, just take off.

454
00:59:59,175 --> 01:00:01,544
It's so weird, I'm like...

455
01:00:01,644 --> 01:00:04,319
I keep on thinking about...

456
01:00:05,181 --> 01:00:08,452
Ever since we were kids
it's been drilled into us that...

457
01:00:08,552 --> 01:00:11,388
our purpose is to explore
the universe, you know.

458
01:00:11,488 --> 01:00:14,290
Outer space is where we'll find...

459
01:00:14,390 --> 01:00:18,600
the answers to why we're here and...

460
01:00:19,128 --> 01:00:21,664
where we come from.

461
01:00:21,764 --> 01:00:24,033
It's like everyone's...

462
01:00:24,133 --> 01:00:29,073
searching for these answers 800
million miles away and the truth is...

463
01:00:29,173 --> 01:00:31,413
the answers are right in front of us.

464
01:00:33,042 --> 01:00:35,017
I know why I'm here.

465
01:00:36,779 --> 01:00:38,820
Me too.

466
01:00:40,683 --> 01:00:42,685
What are we going to do now?

467
01:00:42,785 --> 01:00:47,758
We just spend as much time
here together as we can.

468
01:00:47,858 --> 01:00:51,935
Go to work, act normal, but then...

469
01:00:53,028 --> 01:00:55,236
at night...

470
01:00:55,898 --> 01:00:57,490
we're together.

471
01:00:59,135 --> 01:01:00,976
Okay.

472
01:01:22,992 --> 01:01:25,697
What did you look like
when you were little?

473
01:01:27,663 --> 01:01:30,572
Have you always had these freckles?

474
01:01:32,568 --> 01:01:34,775
I don't know.

475
01:01:35,004 --> 01:01:37,245
I think so.

476
01:01:38,007 --> 01:01:40,977
- Did you grow early?
- Did I grow early?

477
01:01:41,077 --> 01:01:43,285
Yeah, I was tall until I wasn't.

478
01:01:46,349 --> 01:01:48,624
I was a little round kid.

479
01:01:55,992 --> 01:01:58,561
What was your favorite subject?

480
01:01:58,661 --> 01:02:01,395
I liked history. How about you?

481
01:02:02,325 --> 01:02:04,268
I always really loved to write.

