- I always liked to write poetry.

483
01:02:10,840 --> 01:02:14,148
I liked the school trips as well.

484
01:02:14,710 --> 01:02:18,945
When we got to go...
to the great war museum...

485
01:02:19,415 --> 01:02:23,691
to see how the bombs dropped
and wiped out the cities and stuff.

486
01:02:25,254 --> 01:02:27,724
I see a future outside of this room.

487
01:02:27,824 --> 01:02:31,662
Some place out there in the vastness
of everything we know.

488
01:02:32,062 --> 01:02:34,580
In all those millions of miles.

489
01:02:34,680 --> 01:02:38,318
Dominic FYI. The article's finished.

490
01:02:38,868 --> 01:02:41,305
You gave it to me already.
I'm working on it right now.

491
01:02:41,405 --> 01:02:46,147
No, the one after this. On the extraction
of superfluids from neutron stars.

492
01:02:47,843 --> 01:02:49,616
No pressure.

493
01:02:50,279 --> 01:02:53,749
I wish I could explain this
to everyone else.

494
01:02:53,849 --> 01:02:57,421
I'm sick of being...
scared of getting caught.

495
01:02:57,521 --> 01:03:03,165
I want people to know
and not think we're sick.

496
01:03:35,991 --> 01:03:40,664
<i>The significant breakthrough came
with the isolation of the bulbar cell line,</i>

497
01:03:40,764 --> 01:03:43,700
<i>allowing an effective
genetic re-silencing,</i>

498
01:03:43,800 --> 01:03:46,803
<i>without triggering
the systematic organ malfunction</i>

499
01:03:46,903 --> 01:03:49,106
<i>that had marked earlier attempts.</i>

500
01:03:49,206 --> 01:03:52,776
<i>To be clear, this is not
another Kappa Rho inhibitor.</i>

501
01:03:52,876 --> 01:03:57,047
<i>It's a cure that restores the health
and systematic order to the individual.</i>

502
01:03:57,147 --> 01:04:00,262
<i>With the Ashby Eni cure,
it is only a matter of time</i>

503
01:04:00,362 --> 01:04:04,988
<i>before all current S.O.S. cases are
treated, and future cases prevented.</i>

504
01:04:05,088 --> 01:04:07,924
<i>The ENI cure is injected
directly into the neck,</i>

505
01:04:08,024 --> 01:04:12,362
<i>leaving a small coin-like scar,
a quick and simple procedure.</i>

506
01:04:12,462 --> 01:04:16,800
<i>Once administered, the drug requires
a six hour absorption period,</i>

507
01:04:16,900 --> 01:04:19,636
<i>before the disease
is completely neutralized.</i>

508
01:04:19,736 --> 01:04:22,272
<i>After which point, regardless of stage,</i>

509
01:04:22,372 --> 01:04:25,142
<i>the patient is restored to normal health.</i>

510
01:04:25,242 --> 01:04:27,844
<i>Mass production of the drug
is already underway.</i>

511
01:04:27,944 --> 01:04:31,682
<i>And shipments are being made available
to public clinics immediately.</i>

512
01:04:31,782 --> 01:04:35,652
<i>Individuals diagnosed with S.O.S.
need not suffer another day.</i>

513
01:04:35,752 --> 01:04:39,840
<i>Contact your doctor immediately
to receive the Ashby ENI cure...</i>

514
01:04:39,940 --> 01:04:42,875
<i>and rejoin the ranks of equals...</i>

515
01:05:07,083 --> 01:05:09,865
We're gonna remember this feeling.

516
01:05:13,756 --> 01:05:17,278
We're gonna live every day remembering
and we're not gonna feel it.

517
01:05:24,567 --> 01:05:27,043
We're not even gonna exist anymore.

518
01:05:41,183 --> 01:05:43,554
It's not over.

519
01:05:45,321 --> 01:05:47,628
We're not doing that.

520
01:05:52,695 --> 01:05:55,645
- So you don't want the cure.
- No.

521
01:05:56,131 --> 01:05:58,133
Do you?

522
01:05:58,233 --> 01:06:00,108
No.

523
01:06:19,071 --> 01:06:21,312
This is Nia.

524
01:06:23,525 --> 01:06:26,013
We want to go to the Peninsula.

525
01:06:28,097 --> 01:06:32,840
At my old post,
I took part in an air patrol.

526
01:06:33,269 --> 01:06:35,906
We wouldn't fly directly
over the Peninsula, but...

527
01:06:36,006 --> 01:06:39,443
I could see it from a distance.
It's totally overgrown.

528
01:06:39,543 --> 01:06:44,114
If anyone actually lives there
it's in a completely primitive state.

529
01:06:44,214 --> 01:06:47,784
- How do we get there?
- You're seriously considering this?

530
01:06:47,884 --> 01:06:51,388
- We've already decided.
- You know you'll be on your own out there.

531
01:06:51,488 --> 01:06:54,157
There will be no one to look after you.

532
01:06:54,557 --> 01:06:56,893
Whatever we go through
it will be together.

533
01:06:56,993 --> 01:07:00,764
I know how you're feeling,
but you're not thinking of all the risks.

534
01:07:00,864 --> 01:07:05,072
If we stay here we'll be found out.
We'll get the cure.

535
01:07:08,437 --> 01:07:11,223
You know, it's many years ago...

536
01:07:11,323 --> 01:07:15,594
I was not much older than you are now
when I got the bug,

537
01:07:15,694 --> 01:07:19,933
no one even knew
what S.O.S. was back then.

538
01:07:20,033 --> 01:07:24,725
People were getting it, and most
of them would commit suicide.

539
01:07:25,588 --> 01:07:28,991
There was a young man in my living block,

540
01:07:29,091 --> 01:07:32,995
I could tell he was a hider, just like me,

541
01:07:33,095 --> 01:07:36,570
but no one dared mention it back then.

542
01:07:37,299 --> 01:07:38,841
One night...

543
01:07:38,941 --> 01:07:42,205
he knocked on my door
and told me that he and two others...

544
01:07:42,305 --> 01:07:44,908
were going to the Peninsula
and he wanted me to go with him.

545
01:07:45,008 --> 01:07:48,082
Of course, there was no way I was going.

546
01:07:48,744 --> 01:07:51,214
I knew they were headed for their deaths.

547
01:07:51,314 --> 01:07:52,887
Bess.

548
01:07:56,202 --> 01:08:00,778
A few months after he left
were the loneliest I ever felt.

549
01:08:02,091 --> 01:08:05,166
We'd only spoken that one time.

550
01:08:06,695 --> 01:08:10,099
More than all the suicides I've seen.

551
01:08:10,199 --> 01:08:12,903
It was his death that was the most...

552
01:08:13,003 --> 01:08:15,571
unnecessarily wasteful.

553
01:08:15,671 --> 01:08:18,107
Such a waste.

554
01:08:18,207 --> 01:08:20,796
That was a new feeling for me.

555
01:08:22,244 --> 01:08:24,918
But you don't know that he died.

556
01:08:26,382 --> 01:08:28,856
What if he didn't?

557
01:08:41,263 --> 01:08:45,635
I can talk to my old colleague. He was
the pilot who took us on the air patrol.

558
01:08:45,735 --> 01:08:50,444
If they get caught, the whole plan could
be traced back to you or to the group.

559
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:54,586
You said interfering was too risky.

560
01:08:55,277 --> 01:08:59,995
If you make this decision
you know... there is no turning back.

561
01:09:00,095 --> 01:09:02,934
If you do manage to get out...

562
01:09:03,587 --> 01:09:05,961
you can never return.

563
01:09:07,156 --> 01:09:09,363
Of course.

564
01:09:22,371 --> 01:09:26,380
When you get to the border
ask for Oliver, he will fly you.

565
01:09:28,277 --> 01:09:30,613
What if he gets caught?

566
01:09:30,813 --> 01:09:32,231
He won't.

567
01:09:34,683 --> 01:09:36,924
Good luck.

568
01:09:40,055 --> 01:09:41,490
Thank you.

569
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:52,789
Welling is the closest station
to the border.

570
01:09:52,889 --> 01:09:55,972
Trains don't go there until the weekend.
I checked the schedule.

571
01:09:56,072 --> 01:09:58,478
We could leave on Saturday.

572
01:09:59,942 --> 01:10:01,783
Three days.

573
01:10:06,582 --> 01:10:09,423
- You're shaking.
- So are you.

574
01:10:12,421 --> 01:10:15,820
- Are you sure?
- Yes. Are you?

575
01:10:58,600 --> 01:11:01,342
I got a conception summons.

576
01:11:03,972 --> 01:11:05,005
We're leaving in two days.

577
01:11:05,105 --> 01:11:08,061
By the time they come looking
for you we'll be gone. Ignore it.

578
01:11:08,161 --> 01:11:09,980
My tag is blocked,
I'm not gonna get on the train.

579
01:11:10,080 --> 01:11:12,281
I won't make it through
any of the check points.

580
01:11:12,381 --> 01:11:15,088
Look, it's just a summons, right?

581
01:11:16,719 --> 01:11:18,588
It's not like they're going
to inseminate you...

582
01:11:18,688 --> 01:11:22,229
They'll check my blood.
They'll see I have the disease instantly.

583
01:11:22,424 --> 01:11:24,794
Yeah, but they can't force you
to get the cure.

584
01:11:24,894 --> 01:11:27,130
I've been diagnosed,
no one's forcing me to get it, are they?

585
01:11:27,230 --> 01:11:29,598
Besides, the clinics
are overwhelmed right now.

586
01:11:29,698 --> 01:11:33,270
All that's going to happen is, they'll
tell you you've tested positive for S.O.S.,

587
01:11:33,370 --> 01:11:37,866
and that you should see your doctor
immediately, that's it. Then get out of there.

588
01:11:39,308 --> 01:11:41,376
Nothing's changed.

589
01:11:41,476 --> 01:11:45,014
We're leaving Saturday, 10 o'clock train.
You've missed the whole morning of work.

590
01:11:45,114 --> 01:11:47,550
You should get over there right away.
I'll come after my shift.

591
01:11:47,650 --> 01:11:49,652
Meet me behind the clinic.

592
01:11:49,752 --> 01:11:51,342
Okay.

593
01:12:02,864 --> 01:12:05,572
I received a summons.

594
01:12:23,352 --> 01:12:25,488
- Hello, Nia.
- Hello, doctor.

595
01:12:25,588 --> 01:12:28,095
Lie back for me, please.

596
01:12:31,059 --> 01:12:33,096
I'm going to take a sample
of your blood, okay?

597
01:12:33,196 --> 01:12:35,069
Okay.

598
01:12:50,646 --> 01:12:53,049
I have the bug, don't I?

599
01:12:53,799 --> 01:12:56,194
Nia, you're pregnant.

600
01:15:40,349 --> 01:15:42,151
- What is it?
- She's pregnant.

601
01:15:42,251 --> 01:15:46,522
She got called for conception duty and they
found out. They're taking her to the den.

602
01:15:46,622 --> 01:15:48,891
- You need to calm down.
- I'm calm, I'm calm, it's fine.

603
01:15:48,991 --> 01:15:51,294
- When did they take her?
- About an hour ago or something.

604
01:15:51,394 --> 01:15:53,994
- Well, listen, I will contact Bess...
- No, no. No. Not Bess.

605
01:15:54,094 --> 01:15:57,700
- She won't help us. Ask someone else.
- There is no one else. Bess is our only hope.

606
01:15:57,800 --> 01:16:00,336
Listen, you can't be seen
around here like this.

607
01:16:00,436 --> 01:16:02,774
I'm fine, but let me come with you.
Let me help her...

608
01:16:02,874 --> 01:16:05,744
- Go home, I'll contact you. Wait there.
- I can talk to them. Let me go with you.

609
01:16:05,844 --> 01:16:08,338
Don't attempt to see Nia.

610
01:16:08,438 --> 01:16:10,847
Silas, go home. Trust me.

611
01:16:10,947 --> 01:16:13,783
- What are they gonna do to her?
- Just calm down.

612
01:16:13,883 --> 01:16:17,386
You need to stay calm,
or they'll give you the cure.

613
01:16:17,486 --> 01:16:21,428
Give me a couple hours.
Go home and wait there.

614
01:18:28,583 --> 01:18:31,721
- Jonas?
- Get dressed as fast as you can.

615
01:18:31,821 --> 01:18:34,056
And listen to me carefully,

616
01:18:34,156 --> 01:18:37,481
last week, a woman
was brought in called Eva.

617
01:18:37,581 --> 01:18:42,198
She was stage three. Last night she
knotted a garbage bag over her head,

618
01:18:42,298 --> 01:18:44,466
suffocated, she's dead.

619
01:18:44,566 --> 01:18:47,870
Now you... are going
to switch places with her.

620
01:18:47,970 --> 01:18:51,140
Eva didn't kill herself
last night, you did.

621
01:18:51,240 --> 01:18:53,409
You are Eva, she was you.

622
01:18:53,509 --> 01:18:55,944
- You're gonna walk out of here.
- Just...

623
01:18:56,044 --> 01:18:59,714
Hold out your arm. Your left arm please.

624
01:18:59,814 --> 01:19:01,622
Okay.

625
01:19:02,784 --> 01:19:04,971
All right.

626
01:19:06,271 --> 01:19:08,745
You are Eva.

627
01:19:09,791 --> 01:19:12,800
- Got it?
- Ready?

628
01:19:26,541 --> 01:19:30,174
I told Silas to wait at his apartment.
You'll find him there.

629
01:21:39,374 --> 01:21:43,212
<i>The following message is an update
on the security breach at the den.</i>

630
01:21:43,312 --> 01:21:46,649
<i>The Collective wishes to congratulate
health and safety official,</i>

631
01:21:46,749 --> 01:21:50,192
<i>I.D.: 22564943</i>

632
01:21:50,292 --> 01:21:55,124
<i>who alerted authorities to three individuals
operating against protocol at the den.</i>

633
01:21:55,224 --> 01:21:57,827
<i>Two of the three were health
and safety officials,</i>

634
01:21:57,927 --> 01:22:00,329
<i>and the third was a physician at the den.</i>

635
01:22:00,429 --> 01:22:03,900
<i>All are currently safe
and receiving the Ashby ENI cure.</i>

636
01:22:04,000 --> 01:22:07,970
<i>So that they may return to work as
productive equals in the Collective.</i>

637
01:22:08,070 --> 01:22:11,507
<i>The ENI cure will now be required
for those diagnosed with,</i>

638
01:22:11,607 --> 01:22:13,342
<i>or suffering from S.O.S.</i>

639
01:22:13,442 --> 01:22:16,645
<i>And mandatory S.O.S. testing
will begin immediately,</i>

640
01:22:16,745 --> 01:22:21,283
<i>for all health and safety officials
as well as medical professionals.</i>

641
01:22:21,983 --> 01:22:23,792
<i>Welcome...</i>

642
01:22:27,989 --> 01:22:32,027
Her name is Nia. Her ID tag is 34729647.

643
01:22:32,127 --> 01:22:34,701
She writes text for Atmos.

644
01:22:35,430 --> 01:22:38,005
- You said her name was Nia?
- Yes.

645
01:22:40,401 --> 01:22:42,570
Was she brought here yesterday evening?

646
01:22:42,670 --> 01:22:45,745
- Lives at 6L 415?
- That's right.

647
01:22:46,674 --> 01:22:49,015
She died last night.

648
01:22:49,477 --> 01:22:53,186
According to the doctor's notes,
the cause of death was asphyxiation.

649
01:22:55,450 --> 01:22:58,558
Could you... could you check that again?

650
01:23:03,057 --> 01:23:05,098
Yes, that's her.

651
01:23:14,302 --> 01:23:16,143
Sir?

652
01:23:17,405 --> 01:23:19,679
Are you okay?

653
01:23:21,843 --> 01:23:24,384
Do you need some help?

654
01:26:49,984 --> 01:26:52,358
Where have you been?

655
01:26:53,354 --> 01:26:55,229
Hey.

656
01:27:02,163 --> 01:27:04,434
You okay?

657
01:27:13,491 --> 01:27:15,265
Why?

658
01:27:17,478 --> 01:27:20,453
I thought... I thought you were gone.

659
01:27:28,890 --> 01:27:31,719
How long do you have?

660
01:27:31,859 --> 01:27:34,334
Maybe five hours.

661
01:27:44,973 --> 01:27:46,813
Silas.

662
01:27:52,113 --> 01:27:53,920
Hey.

663
01:27:56,250 --> 01:27:58,524
Fight it.

664
01:28:00,154 --> 01:28:04,159
It doesn't matter, it doesn't matter.
Fight it. Okay?

665
01:28:04,859 --> 01:28:07,066
I'm still pregnant.

666
01:28:13,701 --> 01:28:17,370
We're going to get
on the train tomorrow. Okay?

667
01:28:21,309 --> 01:28:23,550
I love you.

668
01:28:25,279 --> 01:28:29,756
I love you, I love you, I love you,
I love you, I love you.

669
01:28:43,865 --> 01:28:47,068
You have to fight it. Just fight it, okay?

670
01:28:47,668 --> 01:28:50,376
I can already tell it's in me.

671
01:28:53,441 --> 01:28:56,978
Just remember... okay?

672
01:28:57,578 --> 01:28:59,452
How?

673
01:29:03,317 --> 01:29:05,658
Remember this feeling.

674
01:29:07,989 --> 01:29:10,863
Just remember what this feels like.

675
01:29:12,360 --> 01:29:16,478
Yeah, just promise me, no matter...

676
01:29:16,578 --> 01:29:20,135
what happens you keep loving me,
no matter what I say,

677
01:29:20,235 --> 01:29:25,040
what I feel or don't feel, I'm still...
I'm still in here trying. Okay?

678
01:29:25,140 --> 01:29:29,044
I'm still in here.
Just don't give up on me.

679
01:29:29,144 --> 01:29:32,732
- Please, don't give up on me.
- I promise.

680
01:29:33,361 --> 01:29:36,141
I promise that I won't...

681
01:30:25,866 --> 01:30:27,574
Silas?

682
01:30:31,739 --> 01:30:33,913
Good morning.

683
01:30:41,482 --> 01:30:43,723
Do you still love me?

684
01:30:50,124 --> 01:30:52,694
I remember I loved you.

685
01:30:53,394 --> 01:30:55,235
But...

686
01:30:57,098 --> 01:30:59,472
I don't feel it anymore.

687
01:31:05,973 --> 01:31:08,347
Do you still want to go?

688
01:31:09,777 --> 01:31:12,084
We made a plan.

689
01:31:19,020 --> 01:31:20,894
Right.

690
01:32:02,129 --> 01:32:07,369
<i>This is a non-local transport serving
outlying regions with three stops.</i>

691
01:32:07,469 --> 01:32:11,812
<i>The final destination port will be
Welling at the outer Peninsula.</i>

692
01:32:11,912 --> 01:32:14,617
<i>This transport is for...</i>

